Export

OAI-PMH

   One can access to the complete OpenBibArt corpus through OAI-PMH (Open
   Archives Initiative Protocol for Metadata Harvesting).

   OpenBibArt's OAI-PMH exposes its metadata in the OAI-DC metadata format
   (basic Dublin Core).

   To harvest OpenBibArt's repository, use the base URL:
   http://www.openbibart.fr/oai/.

OpenSearch

   On an OpenBibArt research results page, you can export the results in
   the XML OpenSearch format.

OpenBibArt's XML format

   On an OpenBibArt bibliographic reference page, you can visualize (and
   download) the XML version of the reference, by clicking on "XML" link.

   The base of this format is qualified Dublin Core, added with some
   specific fields.

Zotero

   Zotero is a free biblographic manager, and a Firefox add-on.

   When you are on an OpenBibArt bibliographic reference page, a Zotero
   icon in the URL bar shows that you can import it into your library.

   After clicking on the icon, the record's metadata is automatically
   integrated into your Zotero library.

